Cauliflower Shwarma Bowls
  --Jamie Vespa

Green Tahini Sauce:
1/2 c fresh cilantro leaves
1/2 c fresh parsley leaves
1/4 c tahini (sesame seed paste)
2 tbsp fresh lemon juice
1/2 tsp minced fresh garlic
1/4 tsp ground cumin
1/4 tsp each kosher salt and black pepper

Combine all ingredients in a blender or mini food processor. With motor running, gradually stream in 1/3 c warm water and blend until smooth.

Bowls:
1 tbsp curry powder
2 tsp paprika
1 tsp ground cumin
1 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tsp black pepper
3 tbsp evoo
1 large head cauliflower, chopped into florets
15-oz can chickpeas, rinsed, drained, and patted dry
2 c cooked white basmati rice (sub grain of choice)
Optional toppings: thinly sliced English or Persian cucumber and halved cherry tomatoes

Preheat oven to 425F. Combine curry powder, paprika, cumin, salt, and pepper in a bowl. Spread cauliflower and chickpeas out on two separate rimmed baking sheets (or one large baking sheet if you can fit it all). Toss cauliflower with 2 tbsp of the oil, and chickpeas with remaining 1 tbsp oil. Sprinkle 1 tbsp of the spice mixture over chickpeas, and toss to coat. Sprinkle remaining spice mixture over cauliflower, and toss to coat. Place both baking sheets in the oven, and set timer for 30 min. After 15 min, shake the pan of chickpeas, and give the cauliflower a good toss. Remove chickpeas from the oven when the timer goes off, and let the cauliflower go 5-10 min longer, until the tips of the florets are lightly charred. Prepare bowls by placing 1/2 c cooked rice in 4 bowls. Divide roasted cauliflower and chickpeas evenly over each bowl, along with cucumber slices and/or cherry tomatoes, if using. Drizzle Green Tahini Sauce over everything.

